      <akn:section eId="sec_2_577">
        <akn:num>2-577</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Meeting procedures.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-577_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A meeting may be held by video conference, telephone conference, or other electronic means; provided, that:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-577_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>All provisions of this subchapter shall apply to electronic meetings.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-577_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>E-mail exchanges between members of a public body shall not constitute an electronic meeting.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-577_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>When an emergency meeting is convened, the presiding officer shall open the meeting with a statement explaining the subject of the meeting, the nature of the emergency, and how public notice was provided.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
